{"title_page": "Richard Nowakowski", "text_new": "{{short description|East German boxer}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=October 2018}}\n{{For|the American politicians|Richard C. Nowakowski|Richard B. Nowakowski}}\n{{Infobox boxer (amateur)|\n| name=Richard Nowakowski\n| image= Bundesarchiv Bild 183-Z1122-009, Richard Nowakowski, Zagorski.jpg\n| image_size= 250px\n| caption = Richard Nowakowski (left) in 1981\n| fullname = Richard Nowakowski\n| nicknames = \n| nationality = {{GDR}}\n| weight class = [[Featherweight]]\n| club = Schweriner SC, Schwerin \n| birth_date = {{Birth date and age|1955|9|27|df=y}}\n| birth_place = [[Sztum]], [[Pomorskie]], [[Poland]]\n| death_date =\n| death_place =\n| height = {{height|m=1.74|precision=0}}\n| weight = {{convert|57|kg|lb}}\n| medaltemplates=\n{{MedalCountry|{{GDR}}}}\n{{MedalCompetition|[[Boxing at the Summer Olympics|Olympic Games]]}}\n{{MedalSilver| [[1976 Summer Olympics|1976 Montreal]] | [[Boxing at the 1976 Summer Olympics \u2013 Featherweight|Featherweight]]}}\n{{MedalBronze| [[1980 Summer Olympics|1980 Moscow]] | [[Boxing at the 1980 Summer Olympics \u2013 Lightweight|Lightweight]]}}\n{{MedalCompetition|[[World Amateur Boxing Championships|World Amateur Championships]]}}\n{{MedalBronze| [[1982 World Amateur Boxing Championships|1982 Munich]] | Featherweight}}\n{{MedalCompetition|[[European Amateur Boxing Championships|European Amateur Championships]]}}\n{{MedalGold| [[1977 European Amateur Boxing Championships|1977 Halle]] | Featherweight}}\n{{MedalGold| [[1981 European Amateur Boxing Championships|1981 Tampere]] | Featherweight}}\n}}\n\n'''Richard Nowakowski''' (born 27 September 1955 in [[Sztum]], [[Poland]]) is a retired [[boxing|boxer]] from [[East Germany]], who won the silver medal in the men's [[featherweight]] division (\u2013 57&nbsp;kg) at the [[Boxing at the 1976 Summer Olympics|1976 Summer Olympics]] in [[Montreal, Quebec]], Canada. There he was defeated in the final by [[\u00c1ngel Herrera Vera|\u00c1ngel Herrera]] of [[Cuba]].\n\nFour years later, when [[Moscow]] hosted the Summer Games, Nowakowski competed in the [[lightweight]] category (\u2013 60&nbsp;kg), and captured a bronze medal. This was the same result he attained in 1982 at the [[1982 World Amateur Boxing Championships|World Championships]] in [[Munich]], [[West Germany]].\n\n== Olympic results ==\n'''1976 \u2013 Montreal'''\n\n* Round of 64: bye\n* Round of 32: Defeated [[Ruben Mares]] (Philippines) by decision, 5\u20130\n* Round of 16: Defeated [[Behzad Ghaedi Bardeh]] (Iran) referee stopped contest in third round\n* Quarterfinal: Defeated [[Gheorghe Ciochina]] (Romania) referee stopped contest in third round\n* Semifinal: Defeated [[Leszek Kosedowski]] (Poland) by decision, 5\u20130\n* Final: Lost to [[\u00c1ngel Herrera Vera|\u00c1ngel Herrera]] (Cuba) second-round knockout (was awarded silver medal)\n\n'''1980 \u2013 Moscow'''\n* Round of 32: Defeated [[Christopher Ossai]] (Nigeria) by decision, 5\u20130\n* Round of 16: Defeated [[Geofrey Nyeko]] (Uganda) referee stopped contest in the first round\n* Quarterfinal: Defeated [[George Gilbody]] (Great Britain) by decision, 5\u20130\n* Semifinal: Lost to [[Viktor Demyanenko]] (Soviet Union) referee stopped contest in the first round (was awarded bronze medal)\n\n==References==\n* {{in lang|en}} [https://web.archive.org/web/20070208120758/http://www.databaseolympics.com/players/playerpage.htm?ilkid=NOWAKRIC01 databaseOlympics]\n* {{in lang|de}} [https://web.archive.org/web/20051207024227/http://www.svz.de/sport/wiedererkannt/nowakowski.html Profile on SVZ online]\n* {{in lang|en}} [https://www.sports-reference.com/olympics/athletes/no/richard-nowakowski-1.html sports-reference]\n<br>\n{{Footer European Amateur Champions Featherweight}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Nowakowski, Richard}}\n[[Category:1955 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:People from Sztum]]\n[[Category:German male boxers]]\n[[Category:Sportspeople from Pomeranian Voivodeship]]\n[[Category:Featherweight boxers]]\n[[Category:Lightweight boxers]]\n[[Category:Olympic boxers of East Germany]]\n[[Category:Boxers at the 1976 Summer Olympics]]\n[[Category:Boxers at the 1980 Summer Olympics]]\n[[Category:Olympic silver medalists for East Germany]]\n[[Category:Olympic bronze medalists for East Germany]]\n[[Category:Polish emigrants to East Germany]]\n[[Category:Olympic medalists in boxing]]\n[[Category:Medalists at the 1976 Summer Olympics]]\n[[Category:Medalists at the 1980 Summer Olympics]]\n[[Category:AIBA World Boxing Championships medalists]]\n[[Category:Recipients of the Patriotic Order of Merit in bronze]]\n\n{{Germany-boxing-bio-stub}}\n{{Germany-Olympic-medalist-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{short description|East German boxer}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=October 2018}}\n{{For|the American politicians|Richard C. Nowakowski|Richard B. Nowakowski}}\n{{Infobox boxer (amateur)|\n| name=Richard Nowakowski\n| image= Bundesarchiv Bild 183-Z1122-009, Richard Nowakowski, Zagorski.jpg\n| image_size= 250px\n| caption = Richard Nowakowski (left) in 1981\n| fullname = Richard Nowakowski\n| nicknames = \n| nationality = {{GDR}}\n| weight class = [[Featherweight]]\n| club = Schweriner SC, Schwerin \n| birth_date = {{Birth date and age|1955|9|27|df=y}}\n| birth_place = [[Sztum]], [[Pomorskie]], [[Poland]]\n| death_date =\n| death_place =\n| height = {{height|m=1.74|precision=0}}\n| weight = {{convert|57|kg|lb}}\n| medaltemplates=\n{{MedalCountry|{{GDR}}}}\n{{MedalCompetition|[[Boxing at the Summer Olympics|Olympic Games]]}}\n{{MedalSilver| [[1976 Summer Olympics|1976 Montreal]] | [[Boxing at the 1976 Summer Olympics \u2013 Featherweight|Featherweight]]}}\n{{MedalBronze| [[1980 Summer Olympics|1980 Moscow]] | [[Boxing at the 1980 Summer Olympics \u2013 Lightweight|Lightweight]]}}\n{{MedalCompetition|[[World Amateur Boxing Championships|World Amateur Championships]]}}\n{{MedalBronze| [[1982 World Amateur Boxing Championships|1982 Munich]] | Featherweight}}\n{{MedalCompetition|[[European Amateur Boxing Championships|European Amateur Championships]]}}\n{{MedalGold| [[1977 European Amateur Boxing Championships|1977 Halle]] | Featherweight}}\n{{MedalGold| [[1981 European Amateur Boxing Championships|1981 Tampere]] | Featherweight}}\n}}\n\n'''Richard Nowakowski''' (born 27 September 1955 in [[Sztum]], [[Poland]]) is a retired [[boxing|boxer]] from [[East Germany]], who won the silver medal in the men's [[featherweight]] division (\u2013 57&nbsp;kg) at the [[Boxing at the 1976 Summer Olympics|1976 Summer Olympics]] in [[Montreal, Quebec]], Canada. There he was defeated in the final by [[\u00c1ngel Herrera Vera|\u00c1ngel Herrera]] of [[Cuba]].\n\nFour years later, when [[Moscow]] hosted the Summer Games, Nowakowski competed in the [[lightweight]] category (\u2013 60&nbsp;kg), and captured a bronze medal. This was the same result he attained in 1982 at the [[1982 World Amateur Boxing Championships|World Championships]] in [[Munich]], [[West Germany]].\n\n== Olympic results ==\n'''1976 \u2013 Montreal'''\n\n*1st round bye\n* Round of 32: Defeated [[Ruben Mares]] (Philippines) by decision, 5\u20130\n* Round of 16: Defeated [[Behzad Ghaedi Bardeh]] (Iran) referee stopped contest in third round\n* Quarterfinal: Defeated [[Gheorghe Ciochina]] (Romania) referee stopped contest in third round\n* Semifinal: Defeated [[Leszek Kosedowski]] (Poland) by decision, 5\u20130\n* Final: Lost to [[\u00c1ngel Herrera Vera|\u00c1ngel Herrera]] (Cuba) second-round knockout (was awarded silver medal)\n\n'''1980 \u2013 Moscow'''\n* Round of 32: Defeated [[Christopher Ossai]] (Nigeria) by decision, 5\u20130\n* Round of 16: Defeated [[Geofrey Nyeko]] (Uganda) referee stopped contest in the first round\n* Quarterfinal: Defeated [[George Gilbody]] (Great Britain) by decision, 5\u20130\n* Semifinal: Lost to [[Viktor Demyanenko]] (Soviet Union) referee stopped contest in the first round (was awarded bronze medal)\n\n==References==\n* {{in lang|en}} [https://web.archive.org/web/20070208120758/http://www.databaseolympics.com/players/playerpage.htm?ilkid=NOWAKRIC01 databaseOlympics]\n* {{in lang|de}} [https://web.archive.org/web/20051207024227/http://www.svz.de/sport/wiedererkannt/nowakowski.html Profile on SVZ online]\n* {{in lang|en}} [https://www.sports-reference.com/olympics/athletes/no/richard-nowakowski-1.html sports-reference]\n<br>\n{{Footer European Amateur Champions Featherweight}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Nowakowski, Richard}}\n[[Category:1955 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:People from Sztum]]\n[[Category:German male boxers]]\n[[Category:Sportspeople from Pomeranian Voivodeship]]\n[[Category:Featherweight boxers]]\n[[Category:Lightweight boxers]]\n[[Category:Olympic boxers of East Germany]]\n[[Category:Boxers at the 1976 Summer Olympics]]\n[[Category:Boxers at the 1980 Summer Olympics]]\n[[Category:Olympic silver medalists for East Germany]]\n[[Category:Olympic bronze medalists for East Germany]]\n[[Category:Polish emigrants to East Germany]]\n[[Category:Olympic medalists in boxing]]\n[[Category:Medalists at the 1976 Summer Olympics]]\n[[Category:Medalists at the 1980 Summer Olympics]]\n[[Category:AIBA World Boxing Championships medalists]]\n[[Category:Recipients of the Patriotic Order of Merit in bronze]]\n\n{{Germany-boxing-bio-stub}}\n{{Germany-Olympic-medalist-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Worldlywise", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eOlympic results", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Richard_Nowakowski"}
